        <h1><marquee height="45">Anmitsu</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 pack (12 oz) agar agar jelly cubes</li>
            <li>1 can (15 oz) fruit cocktail, drained</li>
            <li>1 cup sweet red bean paste (anko)</li>
            <li>Mochi balls (store-bought or homemade)</li>
            <li>Shiratama dango (sweet rice dumplings, optional)</li>
            <li>Ice cream (matcha, vanilla, or your favorite flavor)</li>
            <li>Kuromitsu (black sugar syrup) for drizzling</li>
            <li>Kinako (roasted soybean flour) for dusting</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Anmitsu</li>
            <li>Japanese Dessert</li>
            <li>Sweet Red Bean</li>
            <li>Mochi</li>
            <li>Ice Cream</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Prepare the agar agar jelly according to the package instructions. Once set, cut it into cubes.</li>
            <li>In serving bowls, arrange the agar agar jelly cubes, fruit cocktail, mochi balls, and shiratama dango (if using).</li>
            <li>Scoop a generous portion of sweet red bean paste onto the center of each bowl.</li>
            <li>Place a scoop of ice cream next to the red bean paste.</li>
            <li>Drizzle kuromitsu over the top and dust with kinako.</li>
            <li>Serve the Anmitsu immediately and enjoy the delightful combination of textures and flavors!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

